author: CNN
description: Former CDC official Dr. Demetre Daskalakis describes the unusual confusion he saw within a meeting of advisers chosen by US Health and Human Services Secretary Robert F. Kennedy Jr. to guide CDC vaccine recommendations. #cnn #news #health #cdc
title: Ex-CDC official calls out ACIP meeting 'chaos'

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Jake Tapper sits down with former Federal Trade Commissioner Alvaro Bedoya to discuss how the Kimmel controversy can have implications well beyond censorship and the TV business.   #CNN #News
title: 'This is much bigger than late night': Ex-FTC on Kimmel feud's impact on TV business

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump defended Covid-19 vaccinations after vaccine advisers to the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention voted unanimously to shift away from a broad recommendation for the vaccine. The advisers voted to recommend that people who want one must consult with a health care provider, a process known as shared clinical decision-making.
title: Trump defends Covid-19 vaccination after CDC advisers vote

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jake Tapper spotlights CEOs in a money-making dilemma amid the FCC's pressure campaign on ABC and Jimmy Kimmel. #CNN #News
title: 'All of this... is about money': How CEOs try to cash in as Trump attacks free speech

author: CNN
description: In a candid conversation with CNN’s Christiane Amanpour, actor and author Matthew McConaughey reflects on the challenges of living in his faith with those around him.   #CNN #News
title: Matthew McConaughey’s new book, 'Poems & Prayers' reflects his lifelong faith

author: CNN
description: Federal funding cuts to a pediatric cancer network that runs clinical trials have limited potentially life-saving treatments for 5-year-old Juliette Lesko, who has an incurable form of pediatric brain cancer called ependymoma. CNN's Rene Marsh spoke to her parents about their fight to save her life. #CNN #News
title: Cuts to cancer research limit access to life-or-death treatment

author: CNN
description:
Drenching storms turned quiet streets in into rivers of mud in California's San Bernardino County. One motorist was trapped in moments, roads were buried and neighborhoods were cut off. Families had to shelter in place and some vehicles were left temporarily stranded, but no injuries have been reported, officials say.
#News #Cnn
title: Mudslide traps motorist in Southern California

author: CNN
description: Protesters and ICE agents clashed outside of an ICE facility in Broadview, Illinois after demonstrators sat in front of the exit as ICE vehicles were trying to leave. Several people, including two Democratic congressional candidates, were struck by pepper balls and tear gas. In a statement to CNN, ICE blamed the protestors for the events, saying they assaulted agents. #CNN #News
title: Protesters clash with ICE in Illinois

author: CNN
description: Stephen Colbert and Jon Stewart also defended Jimmy Kimmel and free speech during their Thursday night shows, after ABC indefinitely suspended his popular late-night show on Wednesday amid a controversy over recent comments made by the longtime host about the investigation into Charlie Kirk’s suspected killer. #CNN #News
title: Conan O'Brien: 'Anyone with a conscience knows it's wrong' to silence Late Night hosts

author: CNN
description: Experts say “kissing bugs” are now endemic in the US and spreading Chagas. CNN’s Dr. Sanjay Gupta walks us through how the disease is diagnosed and treated. #CNN #News #health #kissingbug #chagas
title: How to diagnosis and treat ‘kissing bug’ disease

author: CNN
description: About 150 activists, including many Israeli Jews, marched toward the Gaza fence, demanding an immediate end to genocide and ethnic cleansing. Police, who had declared the area a closed military zone, arrested 4 people.
title: Israeli activists march to Gaza fence

author: CNN
description: Some have been drawing comparison between President Donald Trump’s anti-media campaign, along with the decision to take Jimmy Kimmel’s late-night talk show off the air, and how media has been silenced in other countries. CNN’s Nathan Hodge explains.
title: Jimmy Kimmel’s sidelining is a familiar script for other countries

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump suggested network broadcast licenses should be revoked if they are overwhelmingly critical of him, dismissing worries that the suspension of Jimmy Kimmel’s show was an attack on free speech.  #CNN #News
title: Trump floats pulling TV licenses if networks are ‘against’ him

author: CNN
description:
CNN’s Elizabeth Wagmeister takes a look back and some of the FCC’s historic rulings regarding indecency and obscenity on radio and television since the 1950’s, and how cultural attitudes have shifted over the years.

#CNN #News #Media #FCC
title: How FCC media regulation has evolved

author: CNN
description: A federal judge rejected President Donald Trump’s 85-page defamation lawsuit against the New York Times. Judge Steven D. Merryday of the US District Court for the Middle District of Florida gave Trump one month to refile the suit.  #CNN #News
title: Judge rejects Trump’s New York Times lawsuit, calling it ‘decidedly improper’

author: CNN
description: About 150 activists, including many Israeli Jews, marched toward the Gaza fence, demanding an immediate end to the conflict. Police, who had declared the area a closed military zone, arrested 4 people. #CNN #News
title: Israeli activists march to Gaza fence

author: CNN
description: Estonian airspace was violated by three Russian jets on Friday, the country’s foreign ministry said, adding that it had summoned Russia’s chargé d’affaires over the incident. CNN military analyst Col. Cedric Leighton (Ret.) reacts to the news.  #CNN #News
title: Estonia says Russian fighter jets violated its airspace for 12 minutes

author: CNN
description: ICE agents detained two parents, who are undocumented Mexican immigrants, and their 22-year-old son outside of Chicago as the family was on their way to celebrate their 10-year-old son’s birthday. #cnn #news
title: ICE detains parents on 10-year-old son's birthday

author: CNN
description: Albania's parliament was addressed by its first AI "minister" on Thursday. Diella was appointed by the country's Prime Minister Edi Rama to tackle corruption, but opposition politicians have called the move unconstitutional. #cnn #news
title: Can AI sort out government corruption?

author: CNN
description:
Two families in South Carolina with almost the same last name find each other after generations of separation. The Black Simrils and the White Simrills came from the same plantation more than 200 years ago, and while their shared history is painful, their reunion generations later is full of joy. Watch the full documentary The Simril(l)s: A Family in Black and White on The Whole Story with Anderson Cooper on September 21st at 10pm ET/PT. 

#CNN #News#TheWholeStory
title: Black woman contacted by unknown White relatives

author: CNN
description: Vaccine advisers to the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention voted 11-1 to delay a vote on changes to a newborn hepatitis B shot. CNN’s Meg Tirrell reports on the latest news and Paul Offit, a former member of the CDC vaccine advisers, shares his concerns about Robert F. Kennedy Jr.’s hand-picked vaccine panel.  #CNN #News
title: ‘Our children are going to suffer’: Doctor reacts to CDC vaccine advisers’ meeting

author: CNN
description: Months after the bodies of three young sisters were found abandoned in the Washington state wilderness, authorities believe they’ve found the remains of the man accused of killing them: their father, Travis Decker.
title: Investigators think they’ve found the remains of Travis Decker

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins talks to music legend Willie Nelson about the challenges still facing farmers 40 years on. Nelson is set to perform this weekend at the 40th annual Farm Aid festival, along with Neil Young, John Mellencamp, Dave Matthews and more. "Farm Aid 40" airs live on Saturday, September 20 at 7p ET on CNN. #cnn #cnnnews #farmaid #willienelson
title: Willie Nelson reflects on the 40th anniversary of Farm Aid

author: CNN
description:
Former ABC News anchor and correspondent Terry Moran explained how ABC's indefinite suspension of "Jimmy Kimmel Live" has ripple effects for the free speech of media companies. The network dropped Moran in June after calling President Trump a "world-class hater" online.

#CNN #News #Kimmel #ABC
title: Ex-ABC anchor sounds alarm on Kimmel suspension

author: CNN
description: CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down polling on Republican voters’ distrust of US media and how it ties in with ABC’s suspension of Jimmy Kimmel. #CNN #News
title: Harry Enten: ‘Republicans are absolutely loving what is happening to Jimmy Kimmel’

author: CNN
description: On the latest “All Over the Map” CNN's John King speaks to Democrats in Texas’ 35th district who say their voices have been silenced by redistricting efforts in the state.  #CNN #News
title: Texas Democrats say their voices have been silenced by partisan redistricting

author: CNN
description: Jon Stewart, Jimmy Fallon and Seth Meyers defended Jimmy Kimmel during their shows after he was suspended by ABC for comments he made about Charlie Kirk’s suspected killer and what he called the “MAGA gang.” #CNN #News
title: Late-night hosts defend Kimmel, mock Trump

author: CNN
description: Britain’s foreign intelligence service, MI6, is launching a new online portal called Silent Courier, aimed at using the dark web to entice potential spies to send it secrets, particularly targeting Russia. #CNN #News
title: MI6 launches site in dark web to recruit new spies

author: CNN
description: CBS’ Stephen Colbert interviewed CNN’s Jake Tapper about late-night talk show host Jimmy Kimmel’s indefinite suspension by ABC, amidst a pressure campaign from the FCC. #CNN #news
title: Jake Tapper tells Colbert removal of Kimmel ‘direct’ violation of First Amendment

author: CNN
description:
Dr. Sanjay Gupta sits down with public health expert and former CDC director Dr. Thomas Frieden about the critical and often-invisible role of public health, and what he hopes to accomplish with his new book, The Formula For Better Health.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's Chasing Life podcast: http://swap.fm/l/clyt091925

#cnn #news #health #publichealth
title: Why you should care about public health | Chasing Life

author: CNN
description: Comedy Central’s Jon Stewart opened “The Daily Show” with an extended riff sarcastically praising President Donald Trump after fellow talk show host Jimmy Kimmel was suspended by ABC. #CNN #News
title: Jon Stewart sarcastically praises Trump after Kimmel’s suspension

author: CNN
description:
Russian pro-democracy leader Garry Kasparov issued a stark warning as the Trump administration moves to crackdown on negative press.
Writing in The Next Move, Kasparov recalled how a free press briefly flourished after the Soviet collapse, only to be swiftly crushed under Vladimir Putin.   #CNN #News
title: Russian activist Garry Kasparov warns Trump’s media crackdown echoes Putin’s early rule

author: CNN
description:
The Federal Reserve cut interest rates on Wednesday for the first time this year, a move that could provide some relief for Americans from the higher cost of living. But there is a deepening inequality among households in the United States.

Consumer spending, which is a crucial part of the US economy, accounting for about two-thirds of its growth remains robust: Sales were up a strong 0.6% in August, a month when spending was expected to be somewhat lackluster. #CNN #News
title: Trump claimed he 'solved inflation,' but it has been worsening since May

author: CNN
description: During a House Oversight hearing Thursday with Washington, DC officials, GOP Rep. Nancy Mace interrogated Mayor Muriel Bowser about city laws she believes are too focused on diversity. The exchange devolved into Mace getting into the issue of transgender identity, asking Bowser if she could define what a woman is.
title: ‘I’m a woman. Are you a woman?': DC mayor fires back at Mace

author: CNN
description: House Republicans blocked Democrats from subpoenaing FCC Chairman Brendan Carr over ABC’s suspension of Jimmy Kimmel. Democratic Rep. Ro Khanna, who pushed for the subpoena, accused the Trump administration of trying to “make comedy illegal.” CNN’s Erin Burnett discusses the clash with Democratic strategist Jamal Simmons and Republican strategist Doug Heye.   #CNN #News
title: GOP lawmakers reject effort to subpoena FCC chief in Kimmel case

author: CNN
description: Sesame Workshop has teamed up with the Pentagon’s Office of Military Family and Community Policy to roll out Healthy, Happy, Ready. The initiative provides new digital tools to help military kids develop strong habits around wellness, movement, and nutrition, and to better handle the strains of military life.   #CNN #News
title: How 'Sesame Street' and Elmo offer support for military families

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said he thinks networks’ broadcast licenses could be revoked if they air overwhelmingly negative perspectives on him. CNN's Kaitlan Collins reports.
title: Trump floats pulling TV licenses over negative coverage of him

author: CNN
description: CNN's Fareed Zakaria asks former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton about Jimmy Kimmel's show being pulled from ABC's air. Watch Fareed Zakaria GPS on Sunday at 10aET/PT.
title: Hillary Clinton reacts to Jimmy Kimmel's suspension

author: CNN
description: Trump and the British prime minister faced questions today on Jeffrey Epstein and last week’s dismissal of ambassador Peter Mandelson, a highly anticipated moment during the president’s England visit; both leaders swiftly moved past the questions.   #CNN #News
title: Trump and Starmer dodge questions on ex-ambassador’s Epstein ties
